summary:
Mojtaba Khamenei, Iran's new Supreme Leader, pledged in his first statement to seal the Strait of Hormuz and target U.S. bases during the ongoing war. This follows disruptions to global oil and gas shipments from the conflict. Commercial ships now avoid the waterway due to fears of Iranian mines, drones, and missiles, further halting tanker traffic. Prolonged blockade risks global energy shortages and price increases affecting consumers worldwide.

A U.S. KC-135 Stratotanker crashed in Iraq during anti-Iran operations, not due to hostile or friendly fire, according to U.S. Central Command. Rescue efforts continue, impacting military logistics. Separately, a pro-Iran militia, Ashab Alkahf, vowed to target French interests after a soldier died and others were wounded in Iraqi Kurdistan; French President Macron condemned the attack following the arrival of a French aircraft carrier. In South Asia, Pakistani jets struck Kabul and Afghan border provinces targeting Pakistani Taliban militants, killing four civilians including women and children, Afghan officials reported; Islamabad cited rising militant attacks from those areas.

Russia tripled strikes on Ukraine's energy infrastructure this winter despite repairs and Western aid, pushing the grid near collapse and affecting millions of civilians. In Congo, Rwanda-backed M23 rebels overran troops and entered Goma, displacing over one million residents inside the city amid gunfire and shelling, according to the U.N. NATO mounted its first coordinated response after a suspected sabotage severed a Baltic Sea cable critical for data and energy links. SpaceX's Crew-10 mission, launched Friday from Kennedy Space Center with NASA, JAXA, and Roscosmos astronauts, expects docking at the International Space Station Saturday to retrieve astronauts stuck nine months. Taiwan's parliament authorized signing stalled U.S. arms deals to bolster defenses. Israel permitted displaced Palestinians to return to northern Gaza after a hostage deal broke a deadlock bisecting a military zone."}
